  "created": "2026-03-16",
  "description": "A sustained visual event at medium density — scanlines crossing at even intervals, modulation steady. Mod wheel increases vizSpeed and pulseAccent, turning the scan from methodical sweep to rapid strobing: the horizontal hold breaks, the image tears across frequencies. Aftertouch drives vizFeedback toward maximum: the display begins sampling its own output, phosphor trails accumulating, image doubling and tripling until the CRT bleeds white at the edges. Velocity selects the initial vizMode — light touch activates mode 0 (raster), medium velocity mode 1 (vector), hard strike fires into mode 2 (spectrum analyzer), each a categorically different visual grammar. Every combination of these three gestures produces a surface that cannot be pre-programmed, only performed.",
